    "Attachment of PEG chains. Increases hydrodynamic radius. Reduces renal clearance. Extends half-life.",
  "agonist-antagonist":
    "Agonist: activates. Antagonist: blocks. Partial agonist: partial activation. Inverse agonist: reduces constitutive activity.",
  "ki-kd":
    "Ki: inhibition constant for antagonist. Kd: dissociation constant for ligand-receptor. Lower = higher affinity.",
  "bbb-peptides":
    "Most peptides cannot cross BBB. Strategies: nasal delivery, CPPs, receptor-mediated transcytosis, nanoparticles.",
  "cyclic-peptide":
    "Peptide with covalent bond connecting N-terminus to C-terminus or side chains. Enhanced metabolic stability. Improved cell permeability.",
  "stapled-peptide":
    "Peptide with hydrocarbon crosslink between non-adjacent side chains. Locks alpha-helical conformation. Enhances binding affinity and cell permeability.",
  "peptide-drug-conjugate":
    "Peptide linked to cytotoxic payload via cleavable linker. Targets specific cells via receptor binding. Releases drug inside target cell.",
  "incretin-effect-2":
    "Oral glucose produces more insulin than IV glucose. Mediated by GLP-1 and GIP. Basis for incretin-based diabetes therapies.",
