    "Spontaneous organization of peptides into ordered structures (nanofibers, hydrogels, micelles) driven by non-covalent interactions.",
  "gpcr-card":
    "G-Protein Coupled Receptor. Seven-transmembrane domain receptor. Largest drug target family. Couples to G-proteins for signal transduction.",
  racemization:
    "Conversion of L-amino acids to D-form. Non-enzymatic at high temperature/pH. Problem in peptide drug storage. Monitored by chiral HPLC.",
  "n-methylation":
    "Methylation of backbone amide nitrogen. Reduces H-bond donor capacity. Improves oral bioavailability. Found in cyclosporine.",
  peptidomimetic:
    "Non-peptide molecule that mimics the biological activity of a peptide. Improved stability and bioavailability. Example: renin inhibitors.",
  conotoxin:
    "Venom peptide from cone snails. Targets ion channels with high specificity. Used as research tools and drug leads. Ziconotide is a conotoxin drug.",
  "snac-card":
    "Sodium N-[8-(2-hydroxybenzoyl)] amino caprylate. Absorption enhancer for oral semaglutide. Protects peptide from gastric degradation.",
