  "peptide-dendrimer":
    "Branched peptide architecture with central core. Multivalent binding. Enhanced avidity. Applications in vaccines and gene delivery.",
  "mirror-phage":
    "Screening D-peptide libraries using D-phage. Produces D-peptide binders resistant to proteolysis. Enantiomeric drug candidates.",
  macrocycle:
    "Ring structure with 12+ atoms. Includes cyclic peptides, depsipeptides, lactams. Conformational constraint enhances binding. Cell permeability challenge.",
  depsipeptide:
    "Peptide containing ester bonds in addition to amide bonds. Found in natural products. Example: dolastatin 10. Enhanced metabolic stability.",
  protac:
    "Proteolysis Targeting Chimera. Bifunctional molecule linking target protein to E3 ubiquitin ligase. Induces protein degradation. Binds catalytically.",
